From tom neumann Subject vw passat again Kojo Yeboah writes KY To all those who have PASSATs do you recommend using Super Unleaded or just KY regular Unleaded I have been using Regular A friend of mine has KY a Jetta and has always used Super Unleaded and thinks I should be using the same KY however I believe the advantages of Super Unleaded for CARs and under KY has been overplayed by guess who the companies who sell them because that is KY where they make the most A Ralph Nader report and other consumer advocates KY have in the past spoken against those oil Your Passat is designed to run on premium gasoline however the engine electronics will retard the timing so that no harm wil be done to the engine with lower octane You will likely however get somewhat more power and fuel mileage especially in hot weather out of this particular engine if you do run it on Tom Neumann DeLuxe I sell Canada Remote Systems Toronto Ontario